"title": "5489: rank",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5489",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A person's seniority and/or status, especially in military, government or priestly positions. Christians should not be concerned about rank or status.</p>\n<h2>Differences in rank amongst those in charge of both military and civil affairs</h2>\n<h3>Emperor</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:1\">LUK 2:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:1\">LUK 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>King</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:3-2Sam5:5\">2SA 5:3–5:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:1\">1KI 4:1</a></p>\n<h3>Judge</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:16-Judg2:19\">JDG 2:16–2:19</a> <em>The book of Judges calls individual judges “deliverers” e.g., <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:9\">3:9</a>, 15.</em></p>\n<h3>Prince</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:15\">JDG 5:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:38\">2SA 3:38</a></p>\n<h3>Leader</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:3-Num2:7\">NUM 2:3–2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:10-Num2:12\">NUM 2:10–2:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:4\">JDG 4:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:1\">1SA 10:1</a></p>\n<h2>Military ranks</h2>\n<h3>Commander</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:8\">2SA 2:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:22\">ACT 24:22</a></p>\n<h3>Captain</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:1\">GEN 39:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:14\">JDG 5:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:9-2Kgs1:13\">2KI 1:9–1:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:3\">ISA 3:3</a></p>\n<h3>Officer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:5\">1KI 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:22\">1KI 9:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:1\">1CH 27:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts25:23\">ACT 25:23</a></p>\n<h3>Centurion</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:5\">MAT 8:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:43\">ACT 27:43</a></p>\n<h2>Civil ranks</h2>\n<h3>Noble</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:3\">EST 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:18\">EST 2:18</a></p>\n<h3>Official</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:1\">1CH 28:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:10\">JER 52:10</a></p>\n<h3>Governor</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:7-1Kgs4:19\">1KI 4:7–4:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:1\">HAG 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:24\">ACT 23:24</a></p>\n<h3>Tetrarch</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:1\">LUK 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>Heads of clans/tribes</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:1\">JOS 14:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:1\">1KI 8:1</a></p>\n<h3>Heads of families</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:2\">NUM 7:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:12-Josh2:13\">JOS 2:12–2:13</a></p>\n<h3>Division of labour involving different degrees of responsibility</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:20-Exod18:23\">EXO 18:20–18:23</a></p>\n<h2>Rank was conferred as a reward</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:5\">1SA 18:5</a></p>\n<h2>Rank within the priesthood</h2>\n<h3>The high priest</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:10\">LEV 21:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num35:25\">NUM 35:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num35:28\">NUM 35:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num35:32\">NUM 35:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:1\">HAG 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:1\">ZEC 3:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:2\">LUK 3:2</a></p>\n<h3>Priests</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:1-Exod28:2\">EXO 28:1–28:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:5-Lev8:12\">LEV 8:5–8:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:16\">NUM 4:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:31\">JOS 22:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:9\">2KI 11:9</a></p>\n<h3>Levites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:26\">EXO 32:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:50\">NUM 1:50</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:18-Deut12:19\">DEU 12:18–12:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:13-2Chr11:14\">2CH 11:13–11:14</a></p>\n<h2>Officers in the NT church</h2>\n<p>In contrast to the priesthood, offices within the NT Church are according to gifts; individuals with different gifts are listed but do not form a hierarchy:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:4-Rom12:8\">ROM 12:4–12:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:28-1Cor12:30\">1CO 12:28–12:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11\">EPH 4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:1\">PHP 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:1-1Tim3:13\">1TI 3:1–3:13</a></p>\n<h3>Some elders are worthy of double honour</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:17\">1TI 5:17</a> <em>Comparison between verses 17 and 28 of <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:1-Acts20:999\">Acts 20</a> shows that the same individuals could be called “elders”, “overseers” or “shepherds” (pastors).</em></p>\n<h3>All believers are called priests</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:5\">1PE 2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:9\">1PE 2:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:6\">REV 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:10\">REV 5:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:6\">REV 20:6</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ taught his disciples not to seek rank or status</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:1-Matt18:4\">MAT 18:1–18:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:33-Mark9:37\">MRK 9:33–9:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:46-Luke9:48\">LUK 9:46–9:48</a></p>",
